claude
______

# Disco Limerick

There once was a dancer named Sue,
Whose disco moves were quite new.
With a spin and a twirl,
She gave boogie a whirl,
And the crowd went wild when she was through.

A DJ named Flash from LA,
Spun records all night and all day.
His beats were so tight,
The floor sparked with light,
As the mirror ball pushed night away.

The disco era, so bold and so bright,
With platform shoes reaching new height.
The dancers would groove,
With their funkiest move,
In a glorious technicolor sight.

