________

**Disco Delight**  

There once was a dance floor so bright,  
Where folks boogied all through the night.  
With mirror balls high,  
And moves that could fly,  
They shimmied with pure disco might!  

The bass line was funky and tight,  
The rhythm just felt so right.  
In platform shoes tall,  
They partied through all,  
Grooving with sheer delight!  

But one day the trend took its flight,  
Though disco still shines in the light.  
For those who recall,  
It’s the best time of all—  
A glittery, groovy sight!

